Jinja2(flask) Syntax:
Block title:
<title>{% block title %} {% endblock %}</title>

Extending template:
{% extend "base.html" %}

If statement:
{% if condition %} {% endif %}

Else statement:
{% if condition %} {% else %} {% endif %}

For statement:
{% for item in list %} {% endfor %}

linking css:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{url_for('static', filename='css/main.css')}}">

CSS properties and values explaination:
display: block;

Explaination: 
This is a block level element this is going to take up the entire width space on the page
aspects of this works in elements like: div, p, h1, footer and form by default.

display: inline;

Explaination:
This an inline level this takes up a small space around a text.
aspects of this works in elements like: span, a and img by default

